creditline: Gift of Elizabeth, Julie, and Catherine Andrus in memory of John and Marion Andrus
description: floral and leaf decorative pattern with two Tritons at center, emerging from vines; one Triton faces out, the other with its back to viewer; two putti holding fronds flank L and R side
marks: Signature, Date monogram and date in plate, bottom center: [1537 /
provenance: John E. Andrus III, Wayzata, Minn.; by descent to his daughters, Elizabeth, Katie, and Julie. Earlier provenances have been gathered, but further research will increase our knowledge of their histories.
title: Ornamental Design with Tendrils, a Couple of Tritons, and Two Children
